title: Independent candidate Ali Muhammad wins NA-23 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Ali Muhammad has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-23 Mardan-III by securing 1,02,175 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party’s candidate Ahmed Khan, who bagged 33,910 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.33 percent.
